cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.MA, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on the application of deep reinforcement learning to solve coordination problems in adversarial team games. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a novel algorithm that uses deep learning techniques. The paper also deals with game theory and coordination, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper mentions the use of exogenous signals, which could be related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
